honeywell.printer.configuration.ez

Class SmartCardConfiguration

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterData
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.PrinterState
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.ez.SmartCardConfiguration
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class SmartCardConfiguration
extends PrinterState
    This class handles the data from an {SC?} query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    CCommand Format
    ENEnabled
    MTMemory Type
    RResponse Format
    SPSmart Card Protocol
    STSmart Card Type
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • SmartCardConfiguration

        public SmartCardConfiguration(ConnectionBase connection)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        connection - connection to printer

        public boolean getCommandFormat_IsPresent()
        Indicates if getCommandFormat() parameter is present.

        This function is useful to determine if the given parameter is supported on the current printer. Because of differences in configuration, hardware or version certain parameter may not exist and the results returned by the parameter getCommandFormat() may not be valid.

        If the parameter is present and valid true, false otherwise.
